# Enter Bubble Navigation

The WYSIWYG editor has two complementary Enter-key navigation systems for escaping nested block containers. Never break one when changing the other.

## Forward Bubble (Exit at End)

Forward bubble exits containers when the user presses Enter repeatedly at the end of the content.

- **List**: 2× Enter (empty LI triggers exit). Handler: `liveWysiwygListEnterExitAttached`.
- **Admonition**: 3× Enter (or 1 with credit). Handler: `liveWysiwygAdmonitionEnterExitAttached`.
- **Blockquote**: 3× Enter (or 1 with credit). Handler: `liveWysiwygBlockquoteEnterExitAttached`.
- **Code block**: 3× Enter (or 1 with credit). Handler: `liveWysiwygCodeBlockEnterExitAttached`.

### Credit chain

When exiting a nested container, the parent container receives credit (`ea.__liveWysiwygAdmonitionEnterCredit` or `ea.__liveWysiwygBlockquoteEnterCredit`) so only 1 more Enter exits the parent. Exiting list→blockquote credits the blockquote. Exiting blockquote→admonition credits the admonition. Exiting admonition→admonition credits the outer admonition.

### Cleanup on exit

Trailing empty paragraphs are removed from the exited container. The cleanup loop **must**:
- Skip `nodeType !== 1` (text nodes, whitespace)
- Skip `.admonition-title` and `.md-admonition-settings-btn` in admonitions
- Only count actual element children as body content

## Reverse Bubble (Exit at Start)

Reverse bubble exits containers and lists when the user presses Enter at position 0 of the first body element or first list item. Handler: `liveWysiwygReverseBubbleAttached`.

### Cases

- **Case A** (non-empty P/heading at start): insert `<p>` before the container. Credit the parent container.
- **Case B** (list as first body child, cursor at start of first LI): insert `<p>` inside the container before the list. Credit the container. Next Enter triggers Case C.
- **Case B (root)** (list at editable-area root, cursor at start of first LI): insert `<p>` before the list at root. No credit (already at root).
- **Case C** (empty P at top with content after it): remove P from container, insert before container. Credit the parent container. This is the hierarchy escalation mechanism.
- **Case D** (code block body, cursor at position 0, code has content): insert `<p>` before the code block / `.md-code-block` wrapper.

### Content guard

Reverse bubble **must not fire** on empty containers or empty lists (no text, only `<br>` / zero-width-space). If the container/list body is empty, Enter is left to browser default so the user can start typing. Case C additionally requires that there is other content after the empty P.

### Hierarchy

Each Enter moves the paragraph one level up the nesting hierarchy until it reaches the editable area root. The handler always targets the **innermost** container. Root-level lists also participate — pressing Enter at the start of the first LI inserts a paragraph before the list.

### Reverse bubble credit chain

When a reverse bubble case exits a nested element, it credits the parent container so that subsequent forward-bubble exits only need 1 more Enter:
- **Case B** (list in container): credits the container (blockquote or admonition) the list is in.
- **Case C** (P exits container): credits the parent container the P is inserted into.
- **Case A** (P inserted before container): credits the parent container the P is inserted into.

### `isAtStartOf` tolerances

The `isAtStartOf` function used by Case B determines whether the cursor is at the start of the first list item. It tolerates:
- Zero-width space markers (`\u200B`, `\u200C`, `\u200D`, `\uFEFF`) at any offset before the cursor in text nodes.
- `<input>` checkbox elements (checklist items) as invisible siblings.
- Whitespace-only text nodes immediately following a checkbox `<input>` as invisible.

### Collapsible admonition support

Container detection uses `isAdmonitionElement()` to recognize both `<div class="admonition ...">` and `<details class="note/warning/...">` elements. Helper functions (`getFirstBodyEl`, `containerHasContent`, `hasContentBeyond`) skip `<summary>` elements (collapsible admonition titles) alongside `.admonition-title` and `.md-admonition-settings-btn`.

## Shift Bypass

`e.shiftKey` cancels both forward and reverse bubbling on **body content only**. When Shift is held, Enter behaves normally (browser default).

**Title handlers must NOT check `e.shiftKey`:**
- Admonition title enter-at-start (inside admonition handler)
- Code block title enter

Title behavior is independent of shift bypass.

## Rules

1. **Do not merge forward and reverse bubble codepaths.** They are independent systems. Editing one must not break the other.
2. **Title vs body separation.** Title enter-at-start handlers and body bubble handlers are independent codepaths. The admonition title handler and code block title handler must remain unaffected by body-level changes.
3. **Handler ordering.** The reverse-bubble handler **must** have higher priority than all forward-bubble handlers (list, admonition, blockquote, code block exit). Priority is enforced by call order in `_editorKeydownRouter` (Tier 3 router in `_setupEditorKeyboard`). See `DESIGN-centralized-keyboard.md`.
4. **Content guard is mandatory.** Reverse bubble must never fire on empty containers. Always check for meaningful content before intercepting Enter.
5. **Credit chain must propagate through nesting.** When exiting a container that is inside a parent container, the parent must receive credit. Verify credit propagation when modifying any exit handler.
6. **Cleanup must filter correctly.** The `bodyEls` population loop in admonition/blockquote exit handlers must skip `nodeType !== 1`, `.admonition-title`, and `.md-admonition-settings-btn`. Failing to filter causes wrong elements to be counted as "empty" and removed.
7. **`stopImmediatePropagation` prevents double-fire.** When any bubble handler fires, it must call `stopImmediatePropagation` to prevent document-level handlers from also responding. The centralized `_editorKeydownRouter` stops dispatching when `e.defaultPrevented` is true after a handler call.
8. **Nav edit mode guard.** All enter-bubble handlers (forward bubble for list/admonition/blockquote/code-block, reverse bubble) must check `_navEditMode` at the top and return early if true. This prevents any content-editing keyboard behavior during nav edit mode. Content is `contenteditable=false` and covered by a read-only overlay during nav edit, but explicit suppression prevents edge-case event leaks from handlers registered on `document` in capture phase.
